144  /// <summary>

238  /// <summary>
239  /// Retrieves the type of unit that is used in a given Category slot for a SystemOfMeasure.
240  /// </summary>
241  /// <param name="system">The system to query</param>
242  /// <param name="category">The category to look up</param>
243  /// <returns>null, if the category is not available in the system, or a UnitOfMeasure otherwise.</returns>
244  public static UnitOfMeasure? GetSystemUnit(SystemOfMeasure system, Category category)
245  {
246  if (SystemUnits.TryGetValue(system, out var sys)
247  && sys.TryGetValue(category, out var unit))
248  {
249  return unit;
250  }
251  else
252  {
253  return null;
254  }
255  }

1650  /// <summary>
1651  /// For a given <see cref="UnitOfMeasure"/>, find any <see cref="Category"/> in any <see
1652  /// cref="SystemOfMeasure"/> which has a matching Category in the given SystemOfMeasure, then
1653  /// retrieve the UnitOfMeasure that fulfills that category in that SystemOfMeasure.
1654  /// </summary>
1655  /// <param name="fromUnit"></param>
1656  /// <param name="toSystem"></param>
1657  /// <returns></returns>
1658  private static UnitOfMeasure FindConversion(UnitOfMeasure fromUnit, SystemOfMeasure toSystem)
1659  {
1660  if (!Conversions.ContainsKey(fromUnit))
1661  {
1662  throw new ArgumentException($"Unit type {fromUnit.ToString()} not recognized for conversion");
1663  }
1664  else if (!TypeGroups.ContainsKey(fromUnit))
1665  {
1666  throw new ArgumentException($"Unit type {fromUnit.ToString()} has not had type groupings defined");
1667  }
1668  else if (!SystemUnits.ContainsKey(toSystem))
1669  {
1670  throw new ArgumentException($"System type {toSystem.ToString()} not specified");
1671  }
1672  else
1673  {
1674  foreach (var g in TypeGroups[fromUnit])
1675  {
1676  foreach (var s in SystemUnits[toSystem])
1677  {
1678  if (g == s.Key)
1679  {
1680  return s.Value;
1681  }
1682  }
1683  }
1684 
1685  throw new ArgumentException($"Unit type {fromUnit.ToString()} does not have a matching conversion in system {toSystem.ToString()}");
1686  }
1687  }

1689  /// <summary>
1690  /// Convert a value from one unit of measure to another.
1691  /// </summary>
1692  /// <param name="value"></param>
1693  /// <param name="fromUnit"></param>
1694  /// <param name="toUnit"></param>
1695  /// <returns></returns>
1696  public static float Convert(this float value, UnitOfMeasure fromUnit, UnitOfMeasure toUnit)
1697  {
1698  if (fromUnit == toUnit)
1699  {
1700  return value;
1701  }
1702  else if (Conversions.TryGetValue(fromUnit, out var forFromUnit)
1703  && Conversions[fromUnit].TryGetValue(toUnit, out var conversion))
1704  {
1705  return conversion(value);
1706  }
1707  else
1708  {
1709  throw new InvalidCastException($"Cannot convert {value.ToString(CultureInfo.CurrentCulture)} in {fromUnit.ToString()} to {toUnit.ToString()}.");
1710  }
1711  }
